Field with NULL value means a field with no value
left blank during record creation

IS NULL and IS NOT operators:

This SQL statement lists all TableName with a NULL value in "column" field:
SELECT column
FROM TableName
WHERE column IS NULL;

This SQL statement lists all TableName with a NOT NULL value in "column" field
SELECT column
FROM TableName
WHERE column IS NOT NULL;

Q. Select all records from the Customers where the PostalCode column is empty.
SELECT * FROM Customers
WHERE PostalCode IS NULL;

Q. Select all records from the Customers where the PostalCode column is NOT empty.
SELECT * FROM Customers
WHERE PostalCode IS NOT NULL;
